				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Router Connection Problems<a name="65570"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 4 04 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Runs in cycles, I do 2 pc x 2 accounts per pc often. Sometimes after a patch its bad for 3 or 4 nights, then smooths out.
<br />

<br />
I have NOT been able to trace it to using EQPlayNice or just using regular windows mode. Often, when I have thought it was a boxing issue, I find out lots of folks are having LD problems.
<br />

<br />
I suspect it is more common with cable modems then DSL, but thats just from my informal surveys.
<br />

<br />
Things that might screw you up are some type of spyware on the network, file sharing (ie Napster type deal) you may have signed on, and active virus protection (autoprotect) enabled while you are playing.
<br />

<br />
Always cut down on the number of active window programs running when playing EQ....especially if boxing. I personally disable Norton anti-virus when I play, but if you regularly go online during EQ sessions, or forget to turn it back on, you are exposing yourself.
<br />

<br />
Also, playing with sound on only one box (or none) for best performance. 
<br />

<br />
Try a search at EQ tech support such as this one:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://help.station.sony.com/esupport/esupport/consumer/esupport.asp?id=GUID6532e75a%5F1630%5F11d9%5F8e6b%5F080020fb302c&amp;resource=&amp;number=4&amp;isExternal=0&amp;nShowFacts=&amp;nShowCause=&amp;nShowChange=&amp;nShowAddInfo=&amp;activepage=statement.asp&amp;bForceMatch=&amp;strCurrentSymptom=ROUTER&amp;searchtype=normal&amp;searchclass=&amp;bnewsession=False&amp;selecttype=match">click</a>
<br />

<br />
That was a search for linksys (copy and paste into browser address).
<br />

<br />
(mod edit: made it a link)</span></td>
