				<td colspan="2"><span>I know it's not the best thing to do, but unfortunately the way EQ works and the many many ports it needs to function, it's one of the best solutions for stable game play. Even the SoE devs have recommended that solution specifically for Linksys routers. I haven't had any issues at all with ye old trusty D-link since I switched. (without triggering) ZA does help, h*ll, opening the ports from the router firewall would be hardly any different than running the game on 98 with no protection at all. I have done several security scans from dslreports.com and found that the triggering open with ZA kept from allowing intrusion. Like anything dealing with the internet, it's use at your own risk. And stay off the cheap Pron sites... heh.
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah, on the XP firewall issue, yes the SP2 version is nice, but a lot of people have still yet to upgrade, and a lot that have, are noting many gaming issues from it.</span></td>
